Some common diseases in Chennai during the summer include dehydration, heatstroke, and waterborne diseases. [1, 2, 3]  
Common summer diseases [4]  

• Dehydration: When the body loses more fluids than it takes in, which can disrupt bodily functions [4]  
• Heatstroke: Also known as hyperthermia, this is one of the most common summer illnesses [2]  
• Waterborne diseases: Caused by contaminated water, these include diarrhea, dysentery, cholera, and typhoid [1, 3]  
• Measles and chickenpox: Viral infections that cause skin rashes, high fever, cough, and watery eyes [1]  
• Food poisoning: A common summer illness [2]  
• Headache: Heat-induced headaches are caused by the body's reaction to heat [5]  

How to prevent summer diseases [1, 3]  

• Drink more fluids 
• Eat small, light, and frequent meals 
• Include fresh fruits and vegetables with more water content 
• Maintain general hygiene 
• Boil water to kill pathogens before consumption 

